After spending an off-season and a year of lock-down on his home trails in Santa Cruz, California, @r_doggystyles, aka Ryan Howard, finally flew the coop to visit a friend and check out their riding scene. With the right mix of features, banter, wildflowers, and local insight to lead the way, any place can become your next epic destination. Watch R-Dog x Beacon Hill, WA now!⁣
⁣
Video By: @mindsparkcinema / @isaacwallenn #RockShox

node.text:
To kick off our Brains Behind the Brand series, we introduce you to Jesse Jakomait, a Senior Design Engineer who has been part of the RockShox team for 11 years. Jesse's love for bikes is amplified by an engineering degree and superhuman mindset that has pushed him to set records and stand on more peaks than anyone we know. World, meet Jesse.⁣
⁣
Video By: @joeyschusler #RockShox

Introducing Fresh Tips starring @mitchropo... a spirited series showing how easy it can be to use time wisely this holiday season to spruce up your sled. How do you turn a massive monolith in the woods into a rideable feature? After some years of building off each other's trail building style and ethos, @hannahbergemann and Brad Walton worked seamlessly together to clear a path for the runout, pack in a smooth transition, build a run-in up top, and even rappel down to scrape moss off the rock. Together, they transformed this mossy hunk of sandstone into the "Iceberg".⁣
⁣
“It's a big, tall, and technical feature. But it doesn't scare me since we built it nicely with a smooth transition and nice run-off. The part of it that’s gnarly, is guinea pigging it for the first time. You kind of have an idea in your mind of what it's going to feel like when you're building it." - @hannahbergemann 
⁣⁣

What is ActiveRide? We built in a little bit of compliance in the all-new Reverb AXS XPLR so you can keep pedaling in the saddle when the going gets rough. When you drop the post, even a millimeter, the post instantly becomes active, providing a little suspension while you pedal. Toward the middle of the travel, you'll find the most suspension in the post. Want it to be firmer? Add air. Softer? Let some out. Use 2x your rider weight in PSI as your baseline set-up in your Reverb AXS XPLR.⁣ Available in 27.2mm diameter and 50mm or 75mm of travel.
⁣
#GoAllWays #XPLRCollection

Just like its big-travel siblings, Rudy offers rebound adjustment to dial in the feel of your fork. What's different is how you access the adjustment. Our engineers designed a new rebound adjustment mechanism that includes a spring to curve around the Maxle insert. Use either the Rebound Adjuster or a 2.5 mm hex wrench to find that perfect feel, click-by-click.
